description: A man suspected of imitating a victim of the deadly virus on a Moscow subway train is arrested.
title: Coronavirus prankster faces five-years' jail for Moscow metro stunt
title_page: Coronavirus prankster faces five-years' jail for Moscow metro stunt - BBC News
maintext: "He is in shock. He came of his own accord, he didn't hide. He did not expect all this. The interrogating officer himself stated that the case will probably be dismissed," Russian news site Gazeta quoted the lawyer as saying.
